==Latin==
===Etymology===
# '''[[Anno]]''' is the [[ablative]] of '''[[annus]]''' (''[[year]])''
# '''[[Domini]]''' is the [[genitive]] of '''[[Dominus]]''' (''the [[Lord]]'')

===Expression===
'''Anno Domini'''

# [[Latin]] for "''in the year of our Lord''", often abbreviated [[AD|A.D.]] or [[AD]] as an abbreviation that is placed before or after a year succeeding the year 1 BC.

